      h1 Data Protection Policy
      h2 Data protection
      p
        | The operators of these pages takes the protection of your personal data very seriously. We will treat your personal data confidentially and in accordance with data protection legislation and this data protection policy.
      p
        | The use of our website is usually possible without providing any personal data. Insofar as personal data (for example, name, address or email addresses) is collected on our pages, this always occurs on a voluntary basis as far as possible. This data will not be disclosed to third parties without your express consent.
      p
        | We would like to point out that data transmission on the Internet (for example, email communications) may give rise to security issues. It is not possible to completely safeguard data against third-party access.
      p  
      h2 Cookies
      p
        | In some instances the website uses cookies. Cookies do not cause any damage to your computer and do not contain any viruses. Cookies help to make our service more user-friendly, efficient and secure. Cookies are small text files that are downloaded onto your computer and stored by your browser.
      p
        | Most of the cookies we use are what are known as “session cookies“. They will be automatically deleted after your visit. Other cookies remain stored on your device until you delete them. These cookies enable us to recognize your browser during your next visit.
      p
        | You can set your browser so that you will be notified about the placing of any cookies and in order to allow cookies only in particular cases, to exclude the acceptance of cookies in certain cases or generally, and to activate the automatic deletion of cookies when the browser is closed. The deactivation of cookies may restrict the functionality of this website.
      p  
      h2 Server Log Files
      p
        | The provider of the pages automatically collects and stores information in server log files, which your browser automatically transmits to us. These are:
      ul
        li type and version of the browser
        li operating system used
        li Referrer URL
        li host name of the accessing computer
        li time of the server request
      p
        | It is not possible for this data to be attributed to any specific person. This data will not be merged with any other sources of data. We reserve the right to subsequently check this data if we become aware of concrete evidence of an illegal use.
      p  
      h2 Contact form
      p
        | If you send us requests via the contact form, your details from the contact form including the contact data provided therein will be stored by us for purposes of processing the request and for any subsequent queries. We will not disclose this data to third parties without your consent.
      p  
